article.headline: William & Mary 59, Jacksonville State 56
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Laimis Kisielius and Adam Payton combined for 38 points and held off Jacksonville State to lead William & Mary to a 59-56 win in the school's Tip-Off Classic on Friday night. The Tribe (2-3) went into halftime up 27-20 and led by as many as 10 points in the second period. The Gamecocks (1-4) came to within one on a 3-pointer by Will Ginn, making it 57-56. Kisielius hit two free throws with 19 seconds to play to keep the Tribe's lead. With four seconds left, Tracy Thomas missed a 3-pointer needed to tie the game for Jacksonville State. Kisielius had 20 for William & Mary and Payton added 18. Dorien Brown led the Gamecocks with 15 points and Erik Adams added 14. William & Mary will play Cornell on Saturday in the finals; Jacksonville State will play VMI in the consolation game.
